      <hedline>
        <hl1>Correction</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 27 Parenting column about seventh-grade handwriting champion at St Pius V Catholic School in Melville, NY (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Parenting column on May 27, about a seventh-grade handwriting champion at a Roman Catholic school, St. Pius V, in Melville, N.Y., misstated the reason for the suspension of several students last year. It was for watching movies or listening to music that had been prohibited by the school, not for their remarks about the school's nuns on MySpace, according to the principal, Sister Maria Dolorosa.</p>
      </block>
